.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "25 April 2024" "1.0" "simple_shell Man_Page"

.SH NAME
simple_shell

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell

.SH DESCRIPTION
The simple_shell program provides a basic command line interface for users to interact with a Unix-like operating system. It allows users to execute simple commands and provides a prompt for input.

.SH COMMANDS
The following commands are supported by the simple_shell program:

.IP "ls"
Lists directory contents.

.IP "echo"
Displays a line of text.

.SH USAGE
To use the simple_shell program, simply execute the following command:

.IP "./hsh"

.SH EXIT STATUS
The simple_shell program will return the following exit status codes:

.IP "0"
For successful execution.

.IP "1"
For an error or failure occurrence.

.IP
In future you will be able to exit the simple shell by typing "exit". 
Pressing Ctrl+D will also exit the shell with exit status 0.

